WEBVTT

00:01.720 --> 00:02.789
- I'VE ALWAYS LOVED YOU.
I NEVER STOPPED LOVING YOU.

00:02.890 --> 00:03.857
WILL YOU STILL MARRY ME?

00:03.960 --> 00:05.655
- YES, I WILL MARRY YOU.
- YEAH?

00:05.760 --> 00:08.558
[cheers and applause]

00:08.660 --> 00:10.378
- I JUST HAVE TO TELL YOU
THAT I GOT INTO CORNELL.

00:10.490 --> 00:13.311
- HADDIE, CONGRATULATIONS.
THAT'S FANTASTIC.

00:13.420 --> 00:15.035
- I'M SO PROUD. I REALLY AM.
- THANK YOU.

00:15.150 --> 00:16.378
- HIS MOTHER'S
BEEN INCARCERATED.

00:16.490 --> 00:17.866
SHE'S RELEASED THE RIGHTS
OF HER CHILD

00:17.980 --> 00:20.141
TO KEEP HIM OUT
OF THE FOSTER SYSTEM.

00:20.260 --> 00:21.909
THIS IS VICTOR.

00:22.020 --> 00:23.282
- HI.

00:23.400 --> 00:27.359
- SARAH BRAVERMAN,
WILL YOU MARRY ME?

00:33.200 --> 00:35.646
- LYLA HERSHFELD.

00:35.750 --> 00:36.819
- [exhales]

00:36.930 --> 00:39.478
MOM, YOU ARE NOT
SERIOUSLY COMPARING

00:39.590 --> 00:42.275
MY RELATIONSHIP WITH MARK
TO LYLA HERSHFELD.

00:42.380 --> 00:44.314
- CROSBY SWORE
SHE WAS THE ONE.

00:44.420 --> 00:46.172
AND THEY BROKE UP
TWO WEEKS LATER.

00:46.280 --> 00:48.999
YET THERE SHE IS FOR ALL
ETERNITY IN OUR FAMILY PICTURE.

00:49.110 --> 00:50.452
- MOM...
[scoffs]

00:50.560 --> 00:51.458
THEY WERE 24.
SHE WORE A CROP TOP.

00:51.560 --> 00:53.596
ANYONE COULD HAVE
SEEN THAT COMING.

00:53.700 --> 00:54.496
MARK AND I ARE ENGAGED.

00:54.600 --> 00:55.521
- UH-HUH, YEAH.
WHERE'S THE RING?

00:55.640 --> 00:57.289
- WE'RE WORKING ON IT.
- YEAH.

00:57.400 --> 00:58.606
- YOU GUYS, BE CAREFUL.

00:58.710 --> 00:59.938
DREW--AMY LIKES YOU
JUST THE WAY YOU ARE.

01:00.060 --> 01:01.288
- MOM, PLEASE.

01:01.400 --> 01:02.628
- SARAH, WOULD YOU NOT
DISTRACT HIM?

01:02.750 --> 01:04.672
HE'S STARTING TO BULK UP
FOR AMY'S HOMECOMING, ALL RIGHT?

01:04.780 --> 01:06.839
SO HOW'S THE JOB HUNT COMING?
- GREAT, DAD, GREAT.

01:06.960 --> 01:08.359
- REALLY?
- NO, DAD.

01:08.480 --> 01:09.617
I'M TRYING TO TRANSITION
OUT OF BARTENDING.

01:09.720 --> 01:11.130
IT'S ROUGH OUT THERE.
- FIVE MORE.

01:11.240 --> 01:12.468
- MOM, PLEASE.

01:12.580 --> 01:13.649
- FAMILY ONLY,
THAT'S THE POLICY.

01:13.760 --> 01:16.479
YOU CAN THANK YOUR BROTHER
CROSBY FOR THAT.

01:23.010 --> 01:25.763
- BROUGHT A CREAMER,
SWEETIE.

01:35.090 --> 01:36.159
HEY.

01:36.260 --> 01:41.095
[indistinct chatter
on television]

01:41.200 --> 01:43.304
- HEY, HONEY,
I MADE BRUNCH.

01:43.410 --> 01:45.378
I MADE FRENCH TOAST
AND BACON.

01:45.480 --> 01:47.163
IT'S WELL-DONE,
THE WAY YOU LIKE IT.

01:47.270 --> 01:49.090
YOU REMEMBER THAT I SAID
I WAS GONNA MAKE BRUNCH?

01:49.210 --> 01:50.518
- YEAH, I'M GOOD
WITH THIS, JULIA.

01:50.620 --> 01:52.303
- HEY, YOUR MOM HAS SPENT
A LOT OF TIME

01:52.420 --> 01:55.241
PUTTING THIS STUFF TOGETHER.

01:55.350 --> 01:57.102
- UM, SWEETIE.

01:57.220 --> 01:59.381
[indistinct chatter
on television]

01:59.490 --> 02:02.459
VICTOR, I WOULD REALLY
APPRECIATE IT IF YOU DIDN'T--

02:02.570 --> 02:03.878
WHEN YOU'RE DONE WATCHING
THE SHOW,

02:03.980 --> 02:06.039
IF YOU DIDN'T WATCH IT
WHEN SYDNEY'S AROUND, OKAY?

02:06.160 --> 02:08.390
- YEAH, COOL.

02:08.500 --> 02:10.388
- HOW COME HE GETS
TO WATCH TV?

02:10.500 --> 02:11.398
- SYD!

02:11.510 --> 02:12.954
- WELL, IT'S NOT FAIR.
- COME HERE.

02:13.060 --> 02:15.335
- AND HOW COME HE GETS TO EAT
IN FRONT OF THE TV, TOO?

02:15.440 --> 02:16.919
- SYDNEY, IT'S BRUNCH.
COME HERE.

02:17.030 --> 02:19.055
SYD, SYD.

02:19.170 --> 02:23.402
[indistinct chatter
on television]

02:23.520 --> 02:24.373
- I DON'T WANNA GO ALL THE WAY
TO BURGER AND PIE.

02:24.480 --> 02:25.822
- WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

02:25.930 --> 02:28.581
BURGER AND PIE IS OUR PLACE.
WE LOVE BURGER AND PIE.

02:28.700 --> 02:29.894
- WHEN I WAS EIGHT YEARS OLD.
- YEAH, HONEY.

02:30.010 --> 02:32.592
DO YOU REMEMBER THAT TIME
SHE LEANED OVER THE BACKSEAT

02:32.700 --> 02:35.009
AND WAS LIKE, "I KNOW,
LET'S GO TO BURGER AND PIE."

02:35.120 --> 02:36.314
- I WAS EIGHT
AND I DON'T CARE.

02:36.430 --> 02:37.658
I HAVE TO SPEND TIME
WITH MY FRIENDS.

02:37.770 --> 02:38.634
THIS IS THE LAST WEEK.

02:38.740 --> 02:40.253
both: LET'S ALL GO
- STOP!

02:40.360 --> 02:41.941
both: TO BURGER AND PIE
- STOP!

02:42.050 --> 02:43.426
IT'S THE LAST WEEK
BEFORE I LEAVE.

02:43.540 --> 02:44.700
- EXACTLY, IT'S TIME
TO SPEND WITH FAMILY.

02:44.810 --> 02:46.539
- HONEY, LOOK, I KNOW THAT
THERE'S A LOT TO DO,

02:46.640 --> 02:49.222
WHICH I WAS THINKING WE SHOULD
MEET BEFORE BURGER AND PIE,

02:49.340 --> 02:50.432
GET YOUR WINTER COAT--
JUST LISTEN.

02:50.540 --> 02:51.814
- NO.
- THAT'S A GREAT IDEA, HONEY.

02:51.930 --> 02:53.955
- GET IT OUT OF THE WAY.
- I CAN'T. I DON'T NEED A COAT.

02:54.070 --> 02:55.230
- DO YOU KNOW HOW COLD
IT IS THERE?

02:55.340 --> 02:56.648
- EVERY OTHER DAY,
I'M WITH THE GRANDPARENTS

02:56.760 --> 02:59.206
OR WITH THE AUNTS OR SOME--
OR IT'S A DUMB PHOTO SHOOT.

02:59.310 --> 03:00.277
I NEED TIME ON MY OWN...

03:00.380 --> 03:01.483
- IT'S NOT A DUMB
PHOTO SHOOT.

03:01.590 --> 03:03.239
- WITH MY FRIENDS.
- OKAY? IT'S REALLY NOT.

03:03.350 --> 03:05.454
ALL OF YOUR GRANDPARENTS,
EVERYBODY WANTS TO SEE YOU.

03:05.560 --> 03:06.720
YOUR AUNTS AND UNCLES, OKAY?
- IT'S FINE.

03:06.840 --> 03:08.387
- EVERYONE'S GE'I'I'ING TOGETHER
FOR YOU.

03:08.490 --> 03:09.764
AND I ALSO THINK THAT YOU SHOULD
SCHEDULE SOME TIME FOR MAX.

03:09.870 --> 03:12.350
- I THOUGHT THAT'S WHAT
BURGER AND PIE WAS.

03:12.460 --> 03:13.734
- NO, BURGER AND PIE
IS FAMILY TIME.

03:13.840 --> 03:15.216
I WANT YOU AND MAX TO HAVE
A LITTLE TIME TOGETHER.

03:15.330 --> 03:16.661
- OKAY, I'LL DO IT.

03:16.780 --> 03:18.600
- YOU HAVE NO IDEA, THOSE
EAST COAST WINTERS ARE BRUTAL.

03:18.710 --> 03:20.325
- UGH.
- MAYBE THAT'S THE REASON

03:20.440 --> 03:21.839
THAT EVERYONE AT CORNELL
KILLS THEMSELVES.

03:21.960 --> 03:23.575
- WIND WHIPS IN YOUR FACE.
- OH, MY GOD.

03:23.680 --> 03:24.578
- THAT'S NOT TRUE, MAX.
- YEAH, IT IS DAD.

03:24.680 --> 03:25.601
- NO, IT'S NOT.
- YES, IT IS.

03:25.720 --> 03:26.880
I SAW IT ONLINE.
- IT'S A RUMOR.

03:26.990 --> 03:28.230
- PEOPLE THERE JUMP OFF--
- HEY, CAN WE STOP?

03:28.340 --> 03:29.614
- YOUR SISTER'S NOT GONNA
JUMP OFF A BRIDGE.

03:29.720 --> 03:32.234
- I'LL JUMP OFF A BRIDGE
IF I STAY HERE.

03:32.350 --> 03:33.271
- YOU NEED A COAT.
- THAT DOESN'T MAKE ANY SENSE.

03:33.380 --> 03:34.927
- EXACTLY.
- EXACTLY.

03:35.040 --> 03:38.009
- ALL I WANT

03:38.110 --> 03:38.895
IS SOMEONE

03:39.010 --> 03:42.559
SOMEONE I CAN HOLD ON

03:42.670 --> 03:45.218
SOMEONE I CAN COUNT ON

03:45.320 --> 03:47.595
SOMEONE TO DANCE
WITH ME

03:52.740 --> 03:54.219
ALL I WANT

03:54.330 --> 03:56.389
IS SOMEONE

03:56.510 --> 03:59.399
SOMEONE I CAN HOLD ON

03:59.510 --> 04:02.479
SOMEONE I CAN COUNT ON

04:02.580 --> 04:06.061
SOMEONE TO DANCE
WITH ME

04:06.170 --> 04:07.512
[band stops playing]

04:07.620 --> 04:09.895
- SORRY TO INTERRUPT THE JAM.
[laughs]

04:10.000 --> 04:10.819
BUT I HAVE LUNCH OPTIONS.

04:10.940 --> 04:13.135
- OH, LOOK WHO IT IS,
MY FAVORITE ITEM

04:13.250 --> 04:15.218
ON THE LUNCHEONE'I'I'E MENU.
- YES--IS ME?

04:15.320 --> 04:16.309
- YOU.
- I AM? [laughs]

04:16.420 --> 04:17.694
- YES.
- GOSH.

04:17.800 --> 04:18.801
IT'S NOT CROSBY?
I MEAN, HE'S PRETTY TASTY.

04:18.910 --> 04:21.526
- YEAH, CROSBY'S PRETTY TASTY,
BUT YEAH.

04:21.640 --> 04:22.800
- I THINK YOU GOT HIM BEAT.
- [laughs] THANK YOU.

04:22.910 --> 04:23.945
- ALL RIGHT. LET'S SEE.

04:24.050 --> 04:25.699
- JUST MAKE SURE YOU WRITE
YOUR NAME NEXT TO IT

04:25.810 --> 04:27.289
BECAUSE OTHERWISE,
I WON'T KNOW WHOSE IS WHICH.

04:27.400 --> 04:29.846
- ALL RIGHT.

04:29.950 --> 04:30.848
YEAH, ALL RIGHT.

04:30.960 --> 04:32.268
THAT LOOKS LIKE
A PRETTY GOOD ORDER.

04:32.370 --> 04:37.307
- YEAH?
- YEAH, SEE IF YOU APPROVE.

04:37.410 --> 04:39.378
- [chuckles]

04:39.480 --> 04:41.619
VERY GOOD CHOICE.

04:41.720 --> 04:43.130
- THANK YOU.

04:43.240 --> 04:45.959
- FOR YOU?

04:55.150 --> 04:57.072
- HELLO.

04:57.190 --> 04:58.088
I'M HERE TO LEAVE A DEPOSIT

04:58.190 --> 04:59.873
FOR THE BRAVERMAN
FAMILY PORTRAIT.

04:59.980 --> 05:01.538
- YOU CAN PUT IT ON THE TABLE.
THANK YOU.

05:01.640 --> 05:03.255
- OVER HERE? OKAY.
- YEAH.

05:03.370 --> 05:04.439
- YOU WON'T FORGET, THOUGH,
RIGHT?

05:04.540 --> 05:05.814
MY MOTHER DOESN'T TRUST
ME WITH THIS.

05:05.920 --> 05:07.330
IT'S SUCH A BIG GROUP
TO GET TOGETHER.

05:07.440 --> 05:09.408
IT'S, LIKE, 17 OR 18 OF US,
WE'RE NOT SURE.

05:09.510 --> 05:10.545
IN FACT, CAN I ASK
YOUR OPINION ACTUALLY,

05:10.650 --> 05:12.163
AS THE FAMILY PORTRAIT GUY?

05:12.270 --> 05:14.955
DO FIANCES NORMALLY GET INCLUDED
IN THE FAMILY PORTRAIT?

05:15.070 --> 05:16.822
- I DON'T REALLY CARE.

05:16.930 --> 05:19.490
17 OR 18--
I DON'T CHARGE BY THE HEAD,

05:19.590 --> 05:20.340
SO IT'S TOTALLY UP TO YOU.

05:20.450 --> 05:23.146
- OKAY.
- OKAY.

05:23.250 --> 05:26.003
- ALL RIGHT. THANKS.

05:30.330 --> 05:32.594
HELP WANTED, HUH?

05:32.710 --> 05:35.292
- YEAH.
- IS THAT FOR REAL?

05:35.400 --> 05:36.492
I MEAN, IT'S JUST SO RETRO,
YOU KNOW,

05:36.610 --> 05:37.941
NOW WITH THE INTERNET.
- YEAH. YEAH.

05:38.060 --> 05:39.436
- I MEAN, DID YOU PUT IT UP
AND FORGET IT WAS THERE--?

05:39.540 --> 05:40.768
- IT'S REAL.
I HAVE IT ON THE INTERNET ALSO.

05:40.890 --> 05:43.541
- YOU NEVER KNOW WHEN
A GENIUS IS GONNA WALK BY.

05:43.650 --> 05:46.027
- UH, SPEAKING OF WHICH,
I, UM--

05:46.130 --> 05:47.233
I'M ACTUALLY
LOOKING FOR A JOB.

05:47.340 --> 05:48.409
WHAT'S THE JOB?
- DO YOU HAVE EXPERIENCE?

05:48.520 --> 05:49.589
- I DO.
- 'CAUSE I NEED SOMEONE

05:49.690 --> 05:51.373
WITH PHOTOGRAPHY EXPERIENCE
ONLY, SO--

05:51.480 --> 05:52.754
- YEAH, OF COURSE.
MY EXPERIENCE IS FROM

05:52.860 --> 05:53.929
A WHILE AGO.
I WORKED IN GRAPHICS AND, UH,

05:54.040 --> 05:56.861
YOU KNOW, MOSTLY
ON ACTUAL FILM PHOTOGRAPHY.

05:56.970 --> 05:58.005
THE WHOLE DIGITAL THING,
NOT SO MUCH.

05:58.110 --> 05:59.179
- WELL, CAN YOU SET UP
A SHOOT?

05:59.280 --> 06:01.521
CHANGE A LENS, LOAD A MEMORY
CARD, ADJUST THE LIGHTS?

06:01.630 --> 06:07.148
- [scoffs]
YEAH, I CAN.

06:07.260 --> 06:08.249
- YOU WORKED IN FILM?

06:08.360 --> 06:10.567
- YEAH, UH, FILM MAINLY.
- THAT'S A PLUS.

06:10.680 --> 06:14.081
THAT'S, UH--I LIKE FILM.

06:14.200 --> 06:16.919
HM.

06:19.130 --> 06:24.022
[grunts]

06:24.140 --> 06:26.199
ALL RIGHT.
- ALL RIGHT?

06:26.310 --> 06:27.208
I CAN INTERVIEW
FOR THE JOB?

06:27.310 --> 06:29.653
- I'LL SEE YOU
TOMORROW AT 2:30.

06:29.760 --> 06:31.102
- YOU HAVE A JOB TOMORROW?

06:31.210 --> 06:32.484
- MM-HMM.
- THAT'S AMAZING.

06:32.590 --> 06:34.103
OH, MY GOD.
WHAT'S THE PAY?

06:34.220 --> 06:35.244
I MEAN, SHOULD WE
DISCUSS TH E--

06:35.360 --> 06:36.384
- LET'S SEE
HOW YOU DO TOMORROW.

06:36.490 --> 06:37.627
- OH, OKAY.
- WE'LL FIGURE IT OUT.

06:37.740 --> 06:38.946
- IT'S A TRIAL PERIOD.
I RESPECT THAT.

06:39.050 --> 06:40.631
I UNDERSTAND THAT.
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

06:40.740 --> 06:41.320
I'M SARAH, BY THE WAY.
- HANK.

06:41.430 --> 06:44.081
- HANK, THIS IS AMAZING.

06:44.190 --> 06:45.293
THIS IS, LIKE, MEANT TO BE.

06:45.400 --> 06:46.606
DON'T YOU THINK?
- OH, WE SHALL SEE.

06:46.710 --> 06:47.881
- SHOULD I TAKE THE SIGN DOWN?
- NO, LEAVE IT.

06:47.990 --> 06:48.911
- ALL RIGHT.

06:49.020 --> 06:50.226
I HAVE A GOOD FEELING
ABOUT THIS.

06:50.340 --> 06:51.329
THANKS, HANK.
- SEE YOU TOMORROW.

06:51.440 --> 06:55.501
2:30, YEAH.

06:55.620 --> 06:58.305
[Lucy Schwartz's
When We Were Young]

07:00.480 --> 07:03.108
WHEN WE WERE YOUNG
WE WERE SMALL

07:03.210 --> 07:06.555
BUT WE DIDN'T
KNOW IT

07:06.660 --> 07:10.380
AH AHH AH

07:10.490 --> 07:13.254
WHEN YOU WERE HURT
YOU WOULD SMILE

07:13.360 --> 07:16.523
SO YOU DIDN'T
SHOW IT

07:16.640 --> 07:19.325
AH AHH AH

07:19.430 --> 07:24.265
AND I

07:24.370 --> 07:27.259
CAN'T BELIEVE YOU'RE MINE

07:30.930 --> 07:34.343
CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'RE MINE

07:35.930 --> 07:39.752
CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'RE MINE

07:42.660 --> 07:44.389
- ALL RIGHT,
NOW, THIS IS GUACAMOLE.

07:44.490 --> 07:45.479
HE WAS MY FIRST LIZARD.

07:45.600 --> 07:47.591
AND AS YOU CAN SEE,
HE'S STILL ALIVE.

07:47.700 --> 07:49.588
- CAN I HOLD HIM?
- NO, IT'S TOO RISKY.

07:49.710 --> 07:50.904
YOU DON'T KNOW
ANYTHING ABOUT HIM.

07:51.980 --> 07:54.608
SYDNEY AND JABBAR
ARE DIFFERENT.

07:54.710 --> 07:57.634
I LET THEM HOLD HIM SOMETIMES.
LIKE, I CAN TRUST THEM.

07:57.750 --> 07:59.468
THEY'VE BEEN AROUND LONGER.

07:59.580 --> 08:00.842
I MEAN, TECHNICALLY
YOU'RE MY COUSIN,

08:00.960 --> 08:02.234
BUT YOU'RE ADOPTED,
SO IT'S DIFFERENT.

08:02.340 --> 08:06.401
I MEAN, YOU'RE NOT REALLY EVEN
PART OF THE FAMILY YET.

08:06.520 --> 08:08.442
LET'S PUT HIM BACK.

08:08.550 --> 08:11.235
NOW LET US SEE
MY GUINEA PIG RUPERT.

08:11.350 --> 08:13.489
- OKAY, MAX.

08:13.590 --> 08:14.864
- I JUST CAN'T BELIEVE
THAT HE HIRED YOU

08:14.970 --> 08:16.449
AND EXPECTS YOU TO GO ON
A PHOTO SHOOT TOMORROW

08:16.560 --> 08:17.720
WITH NO EXPERIENCE.
- WELL...

08:17.840 --> 08:18.761
- THAT'S CRAZY.
- HE DOESN'T EXACTLY KNOW

08:18.870 --> 08:21.805
I HAVE NO EXPERIENCE.
- YOU LIED?

08:21.910 --> 08:24.777
- YOU'VE NEVER LIED
IN A JOB INTERVIEW?

08:24.880 --> 08:27.531
OF COURSE YOU HAVEN'T.
GOD, I DON'T KNOW.

08:27.640 --> 08:30.222
ANYWAY, HE'S A VERY WEIRD,
GRUMPY GUY.

08:30.330 --> 08:31.911
WHO KNOWS IF
IT'LL EVEN WORK OUT?

08:32.020 --> 08:34.466
- WELL, I, UM--
I LOOK FORWARD TO MEETING HIM

08:34.580 --> 08:35.569
AT THE BIG FAMILY PORTRAIT.

08:35.680 --> 08:40.993
- [choking]
- [laughs]

08:41.100 --> 08:42.544
WHAT, ARE YOU CHOKING ON
THAT AWKWARD SEGUE?

08:42.660 --> 08:44.890
- YEAH.
[laughter]

08:45.000 --> 08:48.549
- I PRIDE MYSELF
ON MY AWKWARD SEGUES.

08:48.660 --> 08:52.073
UM, DID YOU, UM--DID YOU
TALK TO YOUR MOM ABOUT IT?

08:52.180 --> 08:54.102
- OF COURSE.
- OKAY.

08:54.220 --> 08:56.313
- LOOK, IT WAS
AN OLD GIRLFRIEND OF CROSBY'S

08:56.430 --> 08:57.567
WHO WRECKED IT
FOR ALL OF US.

08:57.670 --> 08:59.524
MY MOTHER WILL NOT CHANGE
HER MIND. I TRIED.

08:59.640 --> 09:02.700
- OKAY.
IT'S JUST A WEIRD POLICY.

09:02.810 --> 09:06.086
I MEAN...
JUST MAKES ME FEEL LIKE

09:06.200 --> 09:07.428
I-I'M NOT A PART
OF YOUR GUYS' FAMILY...

09:07.540 --> 09:09.019
- OH, MY GOD.
- EVEN THOUGH WE'RE ENGAGED

09:09.130 --> 09:11.018
AND...
- YOU'RE PART OF THE FAMILY.

09:11.130 --> 09:11.983
IT'S A DUMB RULE.

09:12.100 --> 09:13.192
YOU'LL BE IN
THE PICTURE NEXT YEAR.

09:13.310 --> 09:15.062
- OKAY.

09:15.170 --> 09:18.685
DID YOU FIGHT FOR ME?

09:18.790 --> 09:20.929
- OH, HONEY, I DIDN'T REALIZE
IT WAS SO IMPORTANT.

09:21.040 --> 09:23.554
I-I MEAN, I KIND
OF DIDN'T WANT TO GET

09:23.660 --> 09:24.479
INTO A WHOLE THING
WITH HER, SO...

09:24.590 --> 09:28.310
- OH, OKAY.
- I'M SORRY.

09:28.420 --> 09:31.253
- SO KRISTINA WASN'T EVEN
IN THE PICTURE UNTIL THEY WERE--

09:31.360 --> 09:33.009
- NO.
- OKAY, OKAY, OKAY.

09:33.120 --> 09:35.805
- GOOD NIGHT, GRANDMA.
- OH, I LOVE YOU, SWEETIE.

09:35.920 --> 09:37.251
- I LOVE YOU, TOO.
- GIVE ME A KISS.

09:37.360 --> 09:38.531
- BRUSH YOUR TEETH.
- MM.

09:38.640 --> 09:40.631
- OKAY.

09:40.750 --> 09:42.843
- OH, THANKS, MOM.
- I COULD EAT HIM WITH A SPOON.

09:42.960 --> 09:45.508
- MM-HMM, HE'S YUMMY.
- [chuckles]

09:45.610 --> 09:47.020
- YEAH, AND SPIRITUAL.

09:47.130 --> 09:49.951
- HE IS.
- AND--AND--AND PRAYERFUL.

09:52.100 --> 09:54.614
- MOM, WE NOTICED THAT
JABBAR HAS BEEN PRAYING.

09:56.560 --> 09:59.279
- IT IS. IT IS.

09:59.390 --> 10:02.518
- YEAH, UM, WE WERE
JUST A LITTLE BIT CURIOUS.

10:02.630 --> 10:04.734
HE TOLD US
THAT YOU EXPLAINED...

10:04.840 --> 10:10.039
GOD AND HEAVEN
AND PRAYING TO HIM.

10:10.160 --> 10:11.115
- YES, AND?

10:11.230 --> 10:13.391
- AND WE WANT HIM
TO KNOW ABOUT RELIGION.

10:13.500 --> 10:14.910
- ABSOLUTELY, HE MUST.

10:15.020 --> 10:16.191
- HMM.
WELL, MUST HE?

10:16.300 --> 10:17.506
I MEAN, OTHER THAN
ITS HISTORICAL CONTEXT.

10:17.610 --> 10:20.170
