- UH, NO.

19:34.270 --> 19:35.544
- AND YOU RUINED MY BEST SHOT.

19:35.650 --> 19:37.094
- OH, NO, WHAT,
YOUR GOLDEN HOUR?

19:37.210 --> 19:39.542
YOU GOT A MILLION SHOTS OF THAT
FAMILY THAT WERE BEAUTIFUL.

19:39.660 --> 19:40.376
- HERE'S WHAT I'M TALKING ABOUT.
- IF YOU DO NOT LET THAT GO...

19:40.480 --> 19:41.481
- SEE.
- WHAT?

19:41.590 --> 19:42.989
- YOU HAVE NO RESPECT
FOR LIGHT.

19:43.110 --> 19:44.338
- I DO HAVE
RESPECT FOR LIGHT.

19:44.450 --> 19:46.452
IT WAS ONE SHOT OUT OF,
LIKE, 300 GORGEOUS SHOTS.

19:46.560 --> 19:48.596
AND I MEAN, WHAT
DID YOU EXPECT, YOU KNOW,

19:48.700 --> 19:50.429
WITH YOUR ELABORATE
SCREENING PROCESS?

19:50.530 --> 19:51.622
LIKE, YOU DIDN'T EVEN
KNOW MY FIRST NAME.

19:51.740 --> 19:53.526
WHY DIDN'T--WHY DIDN'T YOU
FIRE ME YESTERDAY?

19:53.640 --> 19:57.087
- I NEEDED SOMEBODY
TO HELP ME LOAD THE VAN.

19:57.190 --> 19:59.772
- OH.

19:59.880 --> 20:04.294
- JUST--IT'S--THIS
IS NOT THE JOB FOR YOU,

20:04.410 --> 20:05.604
SO YOU'RE FIRED,
ALL RIGHT?

20:05.720 --> 20:08.268
- FINE.

20:08.370 --> 20:11.476
CAN I AT LEAST
GET MY DAY'S PAY?

20:16.870 --> 20:20.863
- WE EXPLORED OUR SPIRITUAL
SIDE BACK IN THE '605.

20:20.970 --> 20:22.619
- OH, OH, OKAY.
- YES.

20:22.730 --> 20:23.833
- GREAT. WHAT DID YOU--
WHAT DID YOU DO?

20:23.940 --> 20:28.422
- UM, WELL, I LIVED
AND WORKED ON A COMMUNE.

20:28.530 --> 20:30.282
- WOW!

20:30.400 --> 20:31.662
I DID NOT KNOW THAT.

20:31.780 --> 20:35.364
- AND, UM, WE WERE
BUDDHISTS FOR A WHILE.

20:35.470 --> 20:37.199
WE JOINED THE BUDDHIST TEMPLE.

20:37.300 --> 20:40.053
- [chuckles]
YOU WERE A BUDDHIST?

20:40.160 --> 20:42.811
- WHAT?
I CAN BE ZEN.

20:42.930 --> 20:45.854
- AND THERE WAS THAT
TANTRIC THING THAT WE DID.

20:45.960 --> 20:46.858
- OH, YEAH.

20:46.960 --> 20:48.609
- AI Y1 Y1.
MOM, LISTEN.

20:48.730 --> 20:51.301
HERE'S WHAT I'M
TRYING TO GET AT.

20:51.420 --> 20:53.513
YOU KNOW, WHAT DID YOU--
WHAT DID YOU TAKE AWAY

20:53.630 --> 20:55.723
FROM OF ALL OF
THIS EXPERIMENTATION?

20:55.840 --> 20:58.286
- UM, WELL, I THINK
WE BOTH REALIZED

20:58.390 --> 21:01.109
THAT WE WERE MORE
INVESTED IN THIS WORLD

21:01.220 --> 21:03.666
AND THAT IF GOD
EXISTS AT ALL,

21:03.770 --> 21:07.183
HE'S RIGHT HERE IN OUR FAMILY.
YOU KNOW, IN THIS HOUSE.

21:07.300 --> 21:09.700
- OKAY. BUT, YOU KNOW, WHERE
DO YOU THINK WE GO WHEN WE DIE,

21:09.820 --> 21:12.641
OR, YOU KNOW,
WHAT STARTED LIFE?

21:12.750 --> 21:15.127
HOW DO YOU ANSWER
THOSE QUESTIONS?

21:15.230 --> 21:17.881
- I DON'T--I DON'T KNOW.
- I DON'T KNOW.

21:18.000 --> 21:19.570
- AND EVEN IF I DID,
HOW WOULD THAT HELP YOU?

21:19.690 --> 21:22.989
ISN'T THIS SOMETHING THAT YOU
HAVE TO DISCOVER FOR YOURSELF?

21:27.590 --> 21:30.388
- HEY, COME ON. I MEAN,
JEEZ, WE GAVE YOU BASEBALL.

21:30.490 --> 21:34.665
- HM.
THANK YOU FOR THAT.

21:37.050 --> 21:39.109
- BUT YOU KNOW, THINGS HAPPEN.

21:39.220 --> 21:41.700
SO IT'S FINE IF, YOU KNOW,
YOU HAPPENED TO TAKE IT

21:41.810 --> 21:43.493
AND THEN FORGET
TO PUT IT BACK IN THE CAGE.

21:43.610 --> 21:46.397
AND IT'S NOT A BIG DEAL.
- YEAH, NOT A PROBLEM.

21:46.510 --> 21:49.149
WE JUST NEED TO KNOW.
- YEAH.

21:49.270 --> 21:50.817
IT'S FINE.

21:50.930 --> 21:52.238
- I DIDN'T TAKE
HIS STUPID LIZARD.

21:52.340 --> 21:54.717
- OKAY, GOOD.

21:54.830 --> 21:56.092
- WELL, THAT'S ALL
WE NEEDED TO KNOW.

21:56.210 --> 21:58.849
- GREAT. OKAY.

21:58.970 --> 22:02.724
VICTOR, I ALSO
JUST WANTED TO KNOW

22:02.830 --> 22:06.209
HOW IT'S GOING
FOR YOU HERE, OVERALL.

22:06.320 --> 22:09.767
- IT'S FINE.

22:09.880 --> 22:12.326
- GOOD. WELL, YOU KNOW,
IF YOU NEED ANYTHING,

22:12.430 --> 22:14.182
YOU KNOW THAT
WE'RE HERE FOR YOU.

22:14.290 --> 22:16.224
RIGHT?
- YEAH.

22:16.330 --> 22:19.299
- ALL RIGHT.

22:19.400 --> 22:22.028
OKAY.

22:22.130 --> 22:23.472
- DID YOU KNOW THAT

22:23.580 --> 22:25.719
THOUSANDS OF FAMILY PETS
ARE REPORTED MISSING ANNUALLY,

22:25.820 --> 22:28.539
AND METROPOLITAN ZOOS
HAVE SEEN A RISE

22:28.650 --> 22:30.447
IN THEl-T ATTEMPTS
OF EXOTIC ANIMALS.

22:30.550 --> 22:33.371
- MAX, I DON'T WANT TO TALK
ABOUT YOUR STOLEN LIZARD.

22:33.490 --> 22:36.516
I'M GONNA MISS YOU, MAX...

22:36.630 --> 22:38.723
A LOT, ALL THE TIME.

22:38.840 --> 22:43.118
I'M GONNA MISS
HOW YOU'RE REALLY HONEST

22:43.220 --> 22:46.109
AND HOW YOU ALWAYS SAY EXACTLY
WHAT YOU THINK ABOUT THINGS

22:46.220 --> 22:48.427
AND HOW YOU ALWAYS KNOW EXACTLY
HOW YOU FEEL ABOUT THINGS.

22:48.530 --> 22:51.328
IT'S A REALLY RARE QUALITY.

22:51.430 --> 22:53.842
I'M GONNA MISS IT.
- OKAY.

22:57.300 --> 22:58.403
- I GOT YOU A PRESENT.
- DID YOU?

22:58.510 --> 23:01.991
- OOH, NOW HE'S INTERESTED.

23:02.100 --> 23:03.783
_ - YUP!
[grunts]

23:03.890 --> 23:07.166
IT'S A WEIGHTED BLANKET.
- OH, GOODNESS.

23:07.280 --> 23:09.612
- I READ ABOUT IT ONLINE.

23:09.730 --> 23:11.038
UM, IT'S 25 POUNDS,
AND APPARENTLY,

23:11.140 --> 23:14.598
A LOT OF PEOPLE WITH ASPERGER'S
FIND THEM COMFORTING.

23:14.700 --> 23:16.907
SO...YOU WANNA TRY IT?
- SURE.

23:17.010 --> 23:19.763
- [grunts]

23:22.500 --> 23:24.809
[chuckles]

23:28.890 --> 23:30.539
- [sighs]

23:30.650 --> 23:33.289
- HOW'S IT FEEL?

23:33.410 --> 23:34.616
- GOOD.

23:34.720 --> 23:37.928
- GREAT.

23:38.030 --> 23:43.616
ALL RIGHT,
I WILL, UM, LEAVE YOU ALONE.

23:48.180 --> 23:49.932
I LOVE YOU, MAX.

23:54.360 --> 23:56.806
MAX, I SAID I LOVE YOU.

23:56.910 --> 23:58.912
- YEAH. THANKS.

23:59.020 --> 24:02.057
- HMM.

24:05.160 --> 24:06.263
- HEY.

24:06.370 --> 24:08.577
- HEY.

24:08.680 --> 24:10.784
- YOU WAITING UP
FOR HADDIE AGAIN?

24:10.890 --> 24:11.709
- NO.

24:11.820 --> 24:14.687
- NO?
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

24:14.790 --> 24:18.681
- I'M READING.
- MM-HMM.

24:18.800 --> 24:20.825
[sighs]
- I'M PATHETIC.

24:20.940 --> 24:21.861
I'M PATH ETIC.

24:21.970 --> 24:23.278
I DON'T KNOW WHY
I'M WAITING UP FOR HER.

24:23.390 --> 24:25.381
SHE'S GONNA COME HOME,
SHE'S GONNA SAY TWO WORDS TO ME,

24:25.490 --> 24:26.593
AND SHE'S GONNA GO UPSTAIRS.

24:26.700 --> 24:29.760
- WHY DON'T YOU
JUST COME TO BED, HUH?

24:29.880 --> 24:31.529
- I JUST HAD THE BEST WEEK
PLANNED FOR US, YOU KNOW.

24:31.640 --> 24:34.017
WE WERE GONNA DO
SO MANY FUN THINGS.

24:34.120 --> 24:35.564
WE WERE GONNA GO SHOPPING
TOGETHER, AND WE'D HANG OUT,

24:35.680 --> 24:37.841
AND WE'D GOSSIP, AND...

24:37.950 --> 24:40.054
JUST DIDN'T TURN OUT
LIKE THAT AT ALL.

24:40.160 --> 24:42.958
IT WAS LIKE, SHE COULDN'T
FIT ME INTO HER SCHEDULE,

24:43.060 --> 24:44.436
SO IT'S LIKE...
- SHE WENT TO SEE HER FRIENDS.

24:44.550 --> 24:45.642
YOU GOT HER A GOOD COAT.
- I LIKE THE COAT.

24:45.760 --> 24:47.648
- A NICE, WARM COAT.
- IT IS A NICE WARM COAT.

24:47.760 --> 24:49.022
- IT'S GONNA BE COLD.

24:49.140 --> 24:50.892
- AND THE WHOLE THING AT
THE BURGER AND PIE INSTANT--

24:51.000 --> 24:52.035
THAT WHOLE THING
WAS A FIASCO.

24:52.140 --> 24:55.382
- YUP.
- WHO TAKES THAT OFF THE MENU?

24:55.490 --> 24:56.343
- I DON'T KNOW.
IT'S A GOOD BURGER.

24:56.460 --> 24:59.554
- IT'S A GREAT BURGER.
- I KNOW.

24:59.670 --> 25:01.809
I DON'T UNDERSTAND IT.

25:05.500 --> 25:07.013
- SHE'S NEVER GONNA
LIVE HERE AGAIN.

25:10.160 --> 25:11.775
- YEAH.

25:11.880 --> 25:15.577
WELL, SHE'LL COME HOME
FOR HOLIDAYS.

25:15.680 --> 25:18.126
- YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

25:18.240 --> 25:20.686
- YEAH.

25:26.110 --> 25:28.863
- YOU WANNA GET DRUNK?

25:32.080 --> 25:33.388
- KILL IT.

25:33.490 --> 25:35.310
DOWN THE HATCH.
DUMP IT DOWN.

25:35.430 --> 25:36.522
- [laughs]
STOP IT.

25:49.060 --> 25:51.676
- [screams]
GET OFF--G-GUACAMOLE!

25:51.790 --> 25:54.167
- HEY, HEY, HEY.

25:54.270 --> 25:55.476
TODAY IS THE BIG DAY, HUH?

25:55.580 --> 25:57.024
AMY COMES BACK FROM CAMP.

25:57.140 --> 26:00.519
- YEAH, SHE ACTUALLY PUSHED BACK
THE RETURN THREE DAYS, SO...

26:00.620 --> 26:03.271
- SHE DID?
- YEAH.

26:03.380 --> 26:05.655
- AGAIN?
- YEAH.

26:05.770 --> 26:08.147
- HUH.
DID SHE SAY WHY?

26:08.250 --> 26:12.038
- NO, IT'S KIND OF HARD
TO REACH HER OUT THERE.

26:12.150 --> 26:13.139
I MEAN, I DON'T KNOW.

26:13.260 --> 26:14.830
SHE SEEMS KIND OF, LIKE,
DISTANT OR SOMETHING.

26:14.950 --> 26:17.089
WELL, GRANDSON,
I'LL TELL YOU SOMETHING.

26:17.190 --> 26:19.158
HERE'S WHAT I THINK.
[blender grinding]

26:19.260 --> 26:21.637
I'VE SEEN THE WAY
THAT GIRL LOOKS AT YOU.

26:21.750 --> 26:23.604
SHE LOVES TO BE AROUND YOU.

26:23.720 --> 26:25.608
YOU'VE GOT NO WORRIES THERE,
AS FAR AS I CAN SEE.

26:25.720 --> 26:27.267
AS YOU SOON YOU START,
YOU KNOW, BULKING UP,

26:27.370 --> 26:30.954
PUTTING ON SOME WEIGHT,
IT'LL BE--HOO-HOO.

26:31.070 --> 26:35.348
ZEEK'S FAMOUS PROTEIN DRINK
IS SURE TO BULK YOU UP.

26:35.450 --> 26:39.819
DRINK UP.

26:39.940 --> 26:41.009
I TELL YOU WHAT,
I NEED 30 MORE REPS

26:41.110 --> 26:43.977
FROM YOU ON
THE OLD BICEP CURLS, HUH.

26:44.080 --> 26:46.071
ATTA BOY.

26:46.190 --> 26:48.146
- I'M TIRED OF WAKING UP
AND FEELING SO LONELY

26:48.260 --> 26:50.842
I GUESS I SHOULD'VE LISTENED
WHEN YOU SAT DOWN AND TOLD ME

26:50.950 --> 26:54.431
SO GIVE ME ONE MORE DAY

26:54.540 --> 26:56.394
GIVE ME ONE MORE NIGHT

26:56.510 --> 27:00.856
TODAY'S OUR DAY

27:00.960 --> 27:03.781
LET'S FORGET ABOUT
EVERYONE ELSE

27:03.890 --> 27:07.235
AND EVERYTHING ELSE

27:11.000 --> 27:13.241
- CAN YOU BELIEVE
WHAT A PRICK THIS GUY IS?

27:13.350 --> 27:14.419
- YEAH, HE'S THE WORST.

27:14.520 --> 27:16.761
- COMES IN HERE
AND SEDUCES AMBER,

27:16.870 --> 27:18.974
IT TURNS OUT HE'S GOT
A SERIOUS GIRLFRIEND.

27:19.080 --> 27:21.116
ACTS LIKE NOTHING HAPPENED.
REAL CASANOVA, RIGHT?

27:21.220 --> 27:23.836
- RIGHT.
- WHO PULLS CRAP LIKE THAT?

27:23.950 --> 27:25.565
- MUSICIANS.
- YEAH, MUSICIANS.

27:25.670 --> 27:28.150
- EVEN ONES YOU WOULDN'T THINK,
LIKE KENNY G AND STUFF.

27:28.260 --> 27:29.363
- YOU KNOW WHAT? I DON'T WANT
HIM RECORDING HERE ANYMORE.

27:29.470 --> 27:31.609
- WHAT?
- I WANT HIM OUT.

27:31.710 --> 27:33.814
- YOU'RE SERIOUS?

27:33.920 --> 27:35.091
- YEAH, I'M SERIOUS.
- YOU WANT THEM OUT?

27:35.200 --> 27:36.542
I KNEW I SHOULDN'T HAVE
TOLD YOU ABOUT AMBER.

27:36.650 --> 27:38.857
SHE'S 20 YEARS OLD.
SHE'S AN ADULT.

27:38.960 --> 27:40.780
YOU CAN'T GET INVOLVED
LIKE THIS.

27:40.900 --> 27:42.208
- SO WHAT? SO, WHAT,
ARE WE GONNA JUST SIT BACK

27:42.310 --> 27:43.538
AND LET SOMEBODY
TAKE ADVANTAGE OF HER

27:43.660 --> 27:44.547
WITHOUT DOING
ANYTHING ABOUT IT?

27:44.660 --> 27:45.558
I DON'T THINK SO.
- YES.

27:45.660 --> 27:46.581
- YOU KNOW WHAT?
THAT'S IT.

27:46.690 --> 27:47.793
HEY, GUYS, EXCUSE ME.

27:47.900 --> 27:48.889
I WANT YOU...
- HE'S A PAYING CUSTOMER.

27:49.010 --> 27:50.659
- TO PACK IT UP
AND GET OUT.

27:50.770 --> 27:51.794
- WHAT?
- WE'RE DONE HERE.

27:51.910 --> 27:53.070
WE ARE DONE.
- YOU'RE OVERREACTING.

27:53.180 --> 27:54.351
YOU KNOW WHAT--
- YOU'RE DONE.

27:54.460 --> 27:56.496
- YOU'RE NOT TOUCHING
THAT THING ANYMORE.

27:56.600 --> 27:57.498
LISTEN, WHAT ARE YOU--
- HEY.

27:57.600 --> 27:59.807
- ADAM!
- GUYS, I'M SERIOUS.

27:59.910 --> 28:01.798
UNPLUG IT AND GET OUT.
- WHY, MAN?

28:01.920 --> 28:02.944
- WE DON'T WANT YOU HERE.
- OH, MY GOD.

28:03.060 --> 28:04.539
- OKAY? EVERYBODY, OUT.
YOU, GET OUT.

28:04.640 --> 28:05.777
- ADAM!
- YOU KNOW WHAT YOU DID.

28:05.890 --> 28:07.050
- YOU DON'T HAVE
TO LISTEN TO HIM.

28:07.160 --> 28:09.401
- HEY!
- HOW IS SHE GONNA LEARN

28:09.510 --> 28:10.545
A LESSON IF
YOU THROW HIM OUT?

28:10.650 --> 28:13.949
- YOU DON'T HAVE
A DAUGHTER, ALL RIGHT?

28:27.670 --> 28:28.739
- HEY, MARK.

28:28.840 --> 28:32.048
- HI.
- YOU KNOW, SARAH'S NOT HERE.

28:32.150 --> 28:33.356
- I-I KNOW.

28:33.470 --> 28:35.495
I ACT UALLY--I WAS WONDERING
IF I COULD TALK TO YOU.

28:35.610 --> 28:36.702
- OH. WHAT'S UP?

28:36.810 --> 28:40.985
- WELL, CAMILLE...

28:41.090 --> 28:45.811
SARAH AND I ARE ENGAGED,
AS YOU KNOW,

28:45.930 --> 28:47.158
AND I THINK I...
SHOULD BE

28:47.270 --> 28:51.400
IN THE FAMILY PORTRAIT
WITH YOU GUYS.

28:51.520 --> 28:55.138
- OH, MARK,
YOU'RE SO SWEET.

28:55.250 --> 28:56.820
AND WE ALL THINK
YOU'RE WONDERFUL, WE REALLY DO.

28:56.940 --> 28:58.271
IT'S JUST THAT, YOU KNOW,

28:58.390 --> 29:01.382
SOMETIMES LIFE DOESN'T WORK OUT
THE WAY WE EXPECT IT TO.

29:01.490 --> 29:04.004
- 'CAUSE I-I KNOW THAT I DON'T
HAVE A RING YET, OR...

29:04.120 --> 29:06.281
- IT'S NOT ABOUT THE RING.

29:06.390 --> 29:08.119
- WELL, AND I KNOW
THAT WE HAVEN'T SET A--

29:08.220 --> 29:10.290
UM, HEY, ZEEK.
- HEY, MARK.

29:10.400 --> 29:12.812
- I KNOW WE HAVEN'T
SET A WEDDING DATE YET,

29:12.920 --> 29:14.888
BUT DREW IS GRADUATING
THIS YEAR AND WE DIDN'T WANT

29:14.990 --> 29:16.298
TO RUSH INTO IT
UNTIL--BEFORE THAT.

29:16.400 --> 29:19.642
- WELL, RIGHT.
- BUT IT IS GOING TO HAPPEN.

29:19.750 --> 29:22.617
HELLO.
- HI.

29:22.720 --> 29:23.823
- YOU KNOW,
I'M NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

29:23.930 --> 29:25.852
I'M IN LOVE WITH HER.

29:25.970 --> 29:29.519
AND I RESPECT FAMILY POLICY,

29:29.620 --> 29:33.033
BUT I-I AM A PART
OF YOUR FAMILY.

29:33.150 --> 29:37.280
AND I'M PROUD TO BE
A PART OF YOUR FAMILY.

29:37.390 --> 29:40.188
I GUESS I WANT YOU
TO BE PROUD OF IT, TOO.

29:44.050 --> 29:45.529
- MAX, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
MAX, ARE YOU SERIOUS?

29:45.640 --> 29:47.676
MAX! MAX!

29:47.780 --> 29:48.815
DO NOT TOUCH MY STUFF.

29:48.920 --> 29:50.126
- I'M LOOKING FOR GUACAMOLE.
- STOP!

29:50.230 --> 29:51.606
I HAVE TO PACK THIS UP AGAIN.

29:51.720 --> 29:52.709
THIS IS MY STUFF.
- HEY, HEY.

29:52.820 --> 29:54.094
WHAT'S GOING ON IN HERE?

29:54.200 --> 29:55.189
- I'M TRYING TO FIND
ALL THE POSSIBLE...

29:55.310 --> 29:56.334
- MAX IS LOOKING
FOR HIS STUPID LIZARD.

29:56.440 --> 29:57.850
LOOK AT MY ROOM.
- I'LL MAKE MORE LATER.

29:57.960 --> 29:59.302
- HE LOST HIS LIZARD, OKAY.
THIS CAN BE REPACKED.

29:59.410 --> 30:01.207
JUST--I'LL TALK TO HIM.
- OH, GREAT.

30:01.310 --> 30:02.208
I'M SURE THAT
THAT'S REALLY GONNA HELP.

30:02.310 --> 30:03.299
DON'T, IT'S FINE.
- HEY, HADDIE,

30:03.420 --> 30:05.240
JUST TAKE A BREATH.
- I'M PACKING UP.

30:05.350 --> 30:06.658
- NO, IT'S FINE.
- LOSE THE ATTITUDE, OKAY?

30:06.770 --> 30:07.896
- YOU'RE OVERREACTING.
- DON'T--STOP.

30:08.010 --> 30:09.238
STOP. STOP!
I'LL CLEAN IT WHEN I GET BACK.

30:09.350 --> 30:10.931
- WELL, WHERE EXACTLY
DO YOU THINK YOU'RE GOING?

30:11.050 --> 30:12.836
LOOK, YOUR GRANDPARENTS
ARE TH ROWING

30:12.940 --> 30:14.760
A GOING AWAY PARTY FOR YOU,
OKAY? GET BACK HERE.

30:14.880 --> 30:16.279
- THIS ENTIRE PARTY
IS FOR YOU, OKAY?

30:16.400 --> 30:17.731
- YOU'VE KNOWN
ABOUT IT ALL WEEK.

30:17.850 --> 30:18.566
- YOU DON'T JUST WALTZ IN
WHENEVER YOU WANT.

30:18.670 --> 30:20.638
- THIS PARTY IS NOT FOR ME.

30:20.740 --> 30:22.321
NONE OF THIS WEEK
HAS BEEN FOR ME.

30:22.440 --> 30:23.748
I NEED TO GET OUT
AND HAVE A SECOND OF SPACE.

30:23.850 --> 30:25.909
- TAKE A BREATH.

30:26.030 --> 30:27.292
WE'LL REPACK ALL
THIS TOGETHER, OKAY?

30:27.410 --> 30:28.672
- FINE, DON'T COME AT ALL.
DON'T SHOW UP AT ALL.

30:28.790 --> 30:29.996
- COME ON, HONEY. HONEY.
- GREAT, I WON'T!

30:30.100 --> 30:32.261
AND BY THE WAY,
I HAD MY BONDING TIME WITH MAX

30:32.380 --> 30:34.473
AND IT WENT REALLY GREAT,
AND WE'RE CLOSER THAN EVER,

30:34.590 --> 30:37.343
AND HE'S TOTALLY NORMAL.

30:47.530 --> 30:49.350
- [sighs]
HI.

30:49.460 --> 30:51.143
- HI.

30:51.260 --> 30:54.297
- I'M SAYING HI, YOU KNOW,
SO IT'S NOT TOO AWKWARD.

30:54.400 --> 30:59.645
- UM, MIGHT BE
A LITTLE LATE FOR THAT.

30:59.750 --> 31:00.717
- WE'LL JUST GET A LITTLE BIT
MORE, JUST RIGHT ON TOP HERE.

31:00.820 --> 31:06.019
- MY HAIR IS FINE.

31:06.140 --> 31:08.643
- WELL...
[clears throat]

31:08.760 --> 31:10.307
- BOYS.
- YEAH.

31:10.420 --> 31:14.060
HERE, I'LL TAKE THIS
OUT FOR YOU.

31:14.180 --> 31:16.148
- SHE BETTER SHOW UP.

31:16.250 --> 31:17.319
- SHE BETTER SHOW Al-TER
WE MADE ALL THESE CUPCAKES.

31:17.420 --> 31:18.455
- THIS PARTY IS FOR HER,
AND EVERYBODY CAME...

31:18.560 --> 31:20.733
- HEY, HOW DID YOU
HANDLE THE GOD TOPIC WITH

31:20.840 --> 31:22.728
AMBER AND DREW?

31:22.840 --> 31:24.899
- WHICH GOD TOPIC?

31:25.020 --> 31:26.328
- WELL, WE WERE RAISED
IN A SPIRITUAL VACUUM,

31:26.430 --> 31:27.704
SO WHAT DID YOU PASS ON
TO YOUR KIDS?

31:27.810 --> 31:29.675
- OH, CROSBY,
COME ON, LET IT GO.

31:29.780 --> 31:30.678
HEY.
- HEY.

31:30.780 --> 31:32.008
- HOW DID YOU GET IN?

31:32.130 --> 31:32.812
- I KNOCKED AND I RANG,
BUT I DIDN'T THINK...

31:32.920 --> 31:34.808
- WHAT IS THIS?

31:34.920 --> 31:36.740
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?
- WHAT?

31:36.860 --> 31:38.430
- I HAD TO WAIT EIGHT YEARS
TO GET IN THE FAMILY PICTURE.

31:38.550 --> 31:40.950
- YEAH, I HAD TO MARRY
HIS ASS TO GET IN.

31:41.070 --> 31:42.332
- SHE MADE US WAIT UNTIL
OUR TH REE-YEAR ANNIVERSARY.

31:42.450 --> 31:44.589
- HE FOUND A LOOPHOLE!
- THIS IS UNACCEPTABLE.

31:44.690 --> 31:46.419
- YOU GUYS EXAGGERATE
SO BAD.

31:46.520 --> 31:49.865
- WHO'S THAT GUY?
- AUNT SARAH'S FIANCE.

31:49.970 --> 31:54.418
- HUH.

31:54.530 --> 31:54.905
WHAT IS HE, 6?

31:55.010 --> 31:57.319
- HE IS 29.

31:57.430 --> 32:00.422
- YEAH, THAT'S
A LITTLE DARK, MARK.

32:00.530 --> 32:01.667
- YOU'RE A LITTLE WEIRD.

32:01.780 --> 32:04.396
- YEP.
- I LIKE YOU.

32:04.500 --> 32:06.946
- I DON'T KNOW
IF I LIKE YOU YET.

32:07.060 --> 32:09.779
[indistinct chatter]

32:09.890 --> 32:12.404
- MAYBE SOME BLACK OVER HERE.

32:12.510 --> 32:14.478
- HEY, CAN I TALK TO YOU
FOR A SECOND, OUTSIDE?

32:14.580 --> 32:16.229
- UH, YEAH.
- OKAY.

32:16.340 --> 32:19.309
- A RICH, FULL BLUE.
- BUT HIS IS...

32:19.420 --> 32:21.752
- A NAW BLUE.

32:21.870 --> 32:23.007
- I'M SORRY.
I JUST...

32:23.110 --> 32:25.624
- WHAT'S UlIJFl GO AHEAD.

32:25.730 --> 32:27.971
UM, DID YOU TELL THE BAND

32:28.080 --> 32:29.217
THAT THEY COULDN'T RECORD
AT THE STUDIO ANYMORE?

32:29.320 --> 32:30.764
- YEAH.

32:30.870 --> 32:32.007
LOOK, I DIDN'T THINK
THAT NICK BEHAVED

32:32.120 --> 32:35.351
IN AN HONORABLE FASHION, OKAY?

32:35.470 --> 32:37.188
- OKAY, SERGEANT.
I APPRECIATE IT.

32:37.300 --> 32:38.915
BUT WE ARE AT
A RECORDING STUDIO.

32:39.020 --> 32:39.918
- YUP!
- IT'S ROCK AND ROLL.

32:40.020 --> 32:41.248
IT'S...
- I UNDERSTAND IT--

32:41.370 --> 32:42.507
LISTEN, AMBER,
IT WAS MY DECISION,

32:42.610 --> 32:43.463
AND I'M NOT GONNA STAND BY

32:43.580 --> 32:44.672
AND LET SOMEBODY
TAKE ADVANTAGE OF YOU.

32:44.790 --> 32:46.644
OKAY?
- OKAY.

32:46.750 --> 32:49.401
UH, THAT'S NOBLE, BUT I WASN'T
BEING TAKEN ADVANTAGE OF.

32:49.510 --> 32:52.138
I WAS A WILLING PARTICIPANT,
VERY WILLING, OKAY.

32:52.240 --> 32:55.038
AND I'M SORRY, BUT YOU CAN'T
JUMP INTO SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

32:55.140 --> 32:56.300
- THAT GUY WAS A JERK!

32:56.420 --> 32:58.888
- REGARDLESS IF WHETHER
HE WAS A JERK, I'M FINE.

32:59.010 --> 33:01.410
AND YOU THREW AWAY GOOD BUSINESS
FOR NO REASON...

33:01.530 --> 33:02.212
- IT'S NOT ABOUT BUSINESS.
- BECAUSE I'M TOTALLY FINE.

33:02.320 --> 33:04.242
WELL, IT SHOULD BE.

33:04.360 --> 33:05.907
IT'S GOTTA BE,
BECAUSE I'M YOUR EMPLOYEE NOW.

33:06.010 --> 33:07.659
AND YOU HAVE TO START TREATING
ME AS AN ADULT, BECAUSE I AM.

33:07.770 --> 33:11.558
- [sighs]

33:11.670 --> 33:15.128
I'M SORRY.
I REALLY AM.

33:15.230 --> 33:18.154
I CAN SEE HOW THAT WOULD--

33:18.270 --> 33:19.294
I JUST--
I FEEL PROTECTIVE.

33:19.410 --> 33:22.880
I DON'T WANT
TO SEE YOU GET HURT.

33:23.000 --> 33:27.096
YOU UNDERSTAND THAT?

33:27.210 --> 33:31.749
- UNCLE ADAM...
I UNDERSTAND.

33:31.870 --> 33:33.929
I REALLY DO.

33:34.040 --> 33:36.861
BUT CAN YOU PLEASE
DO YOUR BEST

33:36.980 --> 33:38.072
TO TREAT ME
LIKE A NORMAL EMPLOYEE?

33:38.180 --> 33:40.899
- I WILL TRY.
I AM SORRY IF I EMBARRASSED YOU.

33:41.010 --> 33:44.901
- IT'S OKAY.

33:45.020 --> 33:46.248
- WELL, I'M GLAD
YOU CALLED THIS MEETING.

33:46.360 --> 33:47.600
- ME TOO.
THANK YOU, SIR.

33:47.710 --> 33:50.463
- I WILL SEE YOU AT WORK.
- I WILL SEE YOU THERE.

33:50.580 --> 33:53.128
- ALL RIGHT, SHOW UP ON TIME.
- [laughs]

33:53.230 --> 33:55.926
[jazz music playing
in background]

34:06.940 --> 34:09.966
- HEY.

34:10.080 --> 34:15.211
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

34:15.320 --> 34:15.945
- IT'S TOO LOUD IN THERE.

34:16.050 --> 34:19.599
- [chuckles]

34:19.710 --> 34:23.669
YEAH, THEY'RE CRAZY.
- A LITTLE BIT.

34:38.590 --> 34:42.629
- THEY'RE KIND OF
IRREPLACEABLE, THOUGH.

34:45.010 --> 34:47.103
- OOH, BABY.
[cheers and applause]

34:47.220 --> 34:49.871
[indistinct chatter]

34:49.980 --> 34:50.969
- IT'S MY GIRL.

34:51.080 --> 34:52.775
- HEY, HADDIE.

34:52.880 --> 34:54.108
- I GOT HER, GUYS.
I GOT HER.

34:54.230 --> 34:56.425
[indistinct chatter]

34:56.540 --> 34:58.872
- GET IN HERE.
- SHE'S REALLY LATE.

34:58.990 --> 35:01.265
- THAT'S MY GIRL.

35:01.370 --> 35:03.292
[indistinct chatter]

35:03.410 --> 35:05.640
- OKAY, EVERYBODY, LET'S GET
TOGETHER AND GET THIS PHOTO NOW.

35:05.750 --> 35:08.059
- HONEY.
- HM?

35:08.170 --> 35:11.617
- THAT'S OUR BABY.

35:11.730 --> 35:15.063
- IT'S A GOOD TIME
RIGHT NOW, GUYS, OKAY?

35:15.180 --> 35:16.408
- OKAY.
- PERFECT.

35:16.520 --> 35:18.169
- BIGGER SMILE, THOUGH.
- LET'S GO RIGHT NOW.

35:18.280 --> 35:21.215
- WE ARE READY.
- OKAY, MAXY IS GOOD IN HERE?

35:21.320 --> 35:22.969
HE'S GOOD IN HERE
BEHIND THE GRANDPARENTS?

35:23.080 --> 35:25.116
- OKAY.
- LET'S GO RIGHT HERE, GUYS.

35:25.220 --> 35:27.142
GUYS, RIGHT HERE.
WHY DON'T WE DO THIS?

35:27.260 --> 35:30.297
ALL RIGHT,
PRETEND YOU LIKE EACH OTHER.

35:55.320 --> 35:57.242
- THAT'S GOOD.
- YEAH.

35:57.360 --> 35:59.009
- OH, THAT'S BEAUTIFUL.

35:59.120 --> 36:00.428
- YEAH, YOU'RE QUITE A CREW.
- YEAH.

36:00.530 --> 36:01.838
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU GOT EVERYBODY.

36:01.950 --> 36:04.669
- SEE, THAT KID WILL
NEVER LOOK AT THE DAMN LENS.

36:04.780 --> 36:06.395
- YEAH.
- HM.

36:06.500 --> 36:07.603
- YOU DID PRETTY GOOD.
THAT'S MAX.

36:07.710 --> 36:09.393
HE HAS ASPERGER'S.

36:09.510 --> 36:11.432
- OH, YEAH?
- MM-HMM.

36:11.540 --> 36:12.859
- I KNEW SOMETHING WAS UP.

36:12.960 --> 36:15.747
GOOD KID.

36:15.860 --> 36:18.237
- YEAH.

36:18.340 --> 36:19.682
WELL, THANK YOU.

36:19.790 --> 36:21.963
GOD, THESE ARE GREAT.
I COULD LOOK AT THEM ALL DAY,

36:22.070 --> 36:24.630
BUT I SHOULD GET
THESE TO THE FAMILY.

36:24.730 --> 36:27.585
IF ANYONE CAN POSSIBLY
AGREE ON ONE, WE'LL...

36:27.700 --> 36:29.839
- YEAH, LET ME KNOW.
- WE'LL LET YOU KNOW.

36:29.940 --> 36:32.079
YEAH. THANK YOU.
THEY'RE REALLY, REALLY, GREAT.

36:32.190 --> 36:33.999
AND I APPRECIATE IT.

36:34.120 --> 36:35.838
- ALL RIGHT.
- SO, THANK YOU.

36:35.950 --> 36:37.281
- AND YOU CAN TELL YOUR MOM,

36:37.400 --> 36:40.289
YOU KNOW, IF IT DOESN'T WORK OUT
BETWEEN YOU AND JUNIOR,

36:40.400 --> 36:43.779
I COULD JUST PHOTOSHOP HIM OUT
FOR A SMALL MINIMAL COST.

36:43.890 --> 36:45.289
- THANK YOU, THANK YOU SO MUCH.
- YEAH, YEAH.

36:45.410 --> 36:47.162
I'M SURE SHE'LL BE
VERY HAPPY TO HEAR THAT.

36:47.270 --> 36:48.544
- THAT'S ALL RIGHT.
- MM-HMM.

36:48.650 --> 36:49.742
- HE'S A GOOD GUY, RIGHT?
WHERE DID YOU MEET HIM?

36:49.860 --> 36:51.509
IS HE A "MAKE-A-WISH" KID?
- THAT'S GOOD.

36:51.620 --> 36:52.609
THAT'S FUNNY.
- WAS HE TRICK OR TREATING

36:52.720 --> 36:53.687
OR SOMETHING?
- HEY, ENJOY YOURSELF.

36:53.790 --> 36:55.542
THERE'S A LOT
OF MATERIAL THERE.

36:55.660 --> 36:56.752
- [chuckles]
- GOOD-BYE.

36:56.860 --> 36:59.897
- ANYWAY, LOOK,
I WAS GONNA CALL YOU.

37:00.010 --> 37:01.136
- OH, YEAH.
- YEAH.

37:01.250 --> 37:02.558
UM...

37:02.660 --> 37:04.139
TURNS OUT THE PEOPLE
AT THE SHOOT,

37:04.250 --> 37:07.731
THEY LIKED YOU.

37:07.840 --> 37:09.762
THEY, UM, MADE
A BIG STINK ABOUT IT.

37:09.880 --> 37:13.668
SO IT TURNS OUT
YOU'RE GOOD AT THE SCHMOOZE.

37:13.780 --> 37:17.398
AND I HATE TALKING TO CLIENTS.
TRULY, I HATE IT.

37:17.510 --> 37:21.435
I GET A LITTLE SICK
IN MY STOMACH SOMETIMES.

37:21.540 --> 37:24.646
YEAH, SO THAT'S WHY
I WAS GONNA CALL YOU.

37:24.750 --> 37:27.446
YOU'RE NOT AS AWFUL
AS I ORIGINALLY THOUGHT.

37:27.550 --> 37:31.372
- I'M SORRY,
IS THIS...SOME SORT OF

37:31.490 --> 37:33.412
TWISTED JOB OFFER?

37:33.520 --> 37:34.589
- YOU'VE GOTTA LEARN
ABOUT PHOTOGRAPHY, TOO.

37:34.700 --> 37:36.383
YUKKING IT UP WITH CLIENTS,

37:36.490 --> 37:37.593
YOU SMILE--
"HEY, GIVE ME A HUG"--

37:37.700 --> 37:40.282
THAT'S NOT GONNA CUT IT,
I CAN ASSURE YOU THAT.

37:40.390 --> 37:42.358
- I-I WILL LEARN.

37:42.460 --> 37:44.325
- WELL, I'LL CALL YOU, THEN.

37:44.430 --> 37:47.536
LET'S SEE HOW IT GOES.

37:47.640 --> 37:48.629
ALL RIGHT, GO.
GET THE HELL OUT OF HERE.

37:48.740 --> 37:50.776
- THANK YOU S--THANK YOU.
- ALL RIGHT.

38:01.030 --> 38:03.237
- HEY.
- [laughs]

38:03.350 --> 38:04.374
YOU'RE BACK.
- YEAH.

38:04.480 --> 38:06.687
- I CAN'T BELIEVE IT.
- I'M BACK.

38:06.800 --> 38:09.826
- OH, MY GOD.
I MISSED YOU SO MUCH.

38:13.290 --> 38:15.736
- I MISSED YOU, TOO.

38:17.600 --> 38:19.659
- I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU'RE BACK.

38:19.780 --> 38:21.213
DO YOU WANNA
GO INSIDE OR SOMETHING?

38:21.330 --> 38:24.561
- SURE.

38:26.300 --> 38:27.437
- MM!

38:27.540 --> 38:28.768
SHOOTING STAR.
DID YOU SEE IT?

38:28.890 --> 38:29.675
- YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

38:29.790 --> 38:31.189
- OH, MAN.
DID YOU MAKE A WISH?

38:31.300 --> 38:32.619
- YEAH.

38:32.720 --> 38:35.644
- ALL RIGHT, WELL,
DON'T TELL ME WHAT IT WAS.

38:35.760 --> 38:36.920
HEY, WHEN I SAW YOU
PRAYING THE OTHER DAY,

38:37.030 --> 38:41.615
WHAT WERE YOU PRAYING ABOUT?
- DIFFERENT THINGS.

38:41.730 --> 38:43.618
- DIFFERENT THINGS.
WHAT KIND OF THINGS?

38:43.730 --> 38:48.929
- LIKE, I TELL HIM THAT...
TO WATCH OVER MY FAMILY,

38:49.050 --> 38:52.451
FOR US ALL TO BE HAPPY
AND STAY TOGETHER AS A FAMILY.

38:52.570 --> 38:53.730
- OOH, THAT'S NICE.
THAT'S NICE.

38:53.840 --> 38:56.638
- AND A MOTORCYCLE
AND AN XBOX.

38:56.740 --> 38:58.048
- A MOTOR--
YOU CAN'T DRIVE A MOTORCYCLE.

38:58.160 --> 39:01.288
- WHEN I GET OLDER.
- OH, WHEN YOU GET OLDER.

39:01.400 --> 39:03.960
ALL RIGHT,
THOSE ARE GOOD THINGS.

39:04.060 --> 39:07.882
WELL, I KNOW GRANDMA TOLD YOU
WHAT SHE BELIEVES IN,

39:08.000 --> 39:09.092
ABOUT GOD AND RELIGION.

39:09.200 --> 39:11.612
AND I THOUGHT MAYBE I SHOULD
TELL YOU WHAT I BELIEVE.

39:11.720 --> 39:15.440
DO YOU WANNA HEAR IT?
- OKAY, DADDY.

39:15.560 --> 39:18.688
- WELL, I BELIEVE IN YOU.

39:18.800 --> 39:22.281
YOU'RE MY NUMBER ONE GUY.
OKAY?

39:22.390 --> 39:24.551
AND I BELIEVE IN YOUR MOM

39:24.670 --> 39:27.252
AND ALL OF OUR FAMILY,

39:27.360 --> 39:29.282
MY MOM AND DAD
AND MY BROTHERS AND SISTERS.

39:29.400 --> 39:33.632
AND UM, SOMETIMES...

39:33.750 --> 39:35.945
LIKE ON A NIGHT
LIKE TONIGHT,

39:36.060 --> 39:39.609
WHEN I'M SITTING
UNDER THE STARS WITH MY SON,

39:39.720 --> 39:41.335
EATING DELICIOUS COOKIES,
I THINK...

39:41.440 --> 39:47.231
I'M PRETTY BLESSED.

39:47.350 --> 39:50.410
I'M BLESSED BY SOMETHING,
YOU KNOW.

39:50.520 --> 39:53.626
- ME TOO, DADDY.

39:56.800 --> 40:00.042
MM, WHAT'S THAT THING
THAT'S MOVING?

40:00.150 --> 40:04.189
IS THAT ANOTHER SHOOTING STAR?
- THAT'S AN AIRPLANE.

40:04.290 --> 40:05.700
- OHH.
- MM-HMM.

40:05.810 --> 40:08.461
- [exhales]

40:08.570 --> 40:10.982
I JUST NEED HIM TO FEEL
LIKE WE BELIEVE IN HIM.

40:11.090 --> 40:13.809
- [grunts]

40:13.920 --> 40:16.195
IT'S BEEN FIVE MONTHS, JULIA.

40:16.310 --> 40:20.713
YOU CAN'T KEEP WALKING
ON EGGSHELLS AROUND THIS BOY.

40:20.830 --> 40:22.969
- EVERYTHING I'VE READ
SAYS THAT, RIGHT NOW,

40:23.070 --> 40:25.584
OUR JOB IS
TO MAKE HIM FEEL LOVED,

40:25.690 --> 40:27.863
TRUSTED, AND LIKE
HE'S PART OF THIS FAMILY.

40:27.970 --> 40:30.177
- YEAH, AND THE WAY YOU DO THAT
IS TREAT HIM LIKE FAMILY.

40:30.280 --> 40:32.840
NOT ASKING HIM
ABOUT THIS IS LIKE--

40:32.940 --> 40:35.875
IS TREATING HIM LIKE A GUEST.

40:38.150 --> 40:40.220
- GOD.

40:40.330 --> 40:44.391
JOEL...

40:44.510 --> 40:48.332
- WHAT?

40:48.440 --> 40:50.817
- I FEEL LIKE I'M WAITING
TO FALL IN LOVE WITH OUR SON.

41:00.350 --> 41:03.103
[indistinct chatter]

41:11.290 --> 41:13.633
- OKAY.

41:13.740 --> 41:16.982
UM, YOU HAVE EVERYTHING?
YOUR BOARDING PASS, YOUR ID.

41:17.090 --> 41:17.943
- YEAH. YEP!

41:18.060 --> 41:20.221
- YOU GOT ENOUGH CASH?
- YEAH.

41:20.330 --> 41:21.649
- YOU KNOW WHAT? JUST IN CASE.
- YEAH, GIVE HER AN EXTRA $20.

41:22.850 --> 41:23.714
- AND I PACKED YOUR SNACKS
IN YOUR BAG.

41:23.820 --> 41:24.809
- JUST TAKE IT ALL.
- THANKS.

41:24.930 --> 41:26.955
- JUST TAKE ALL OF IT.
- OKAY.

41:27.070 --> 41:28.025
ALL RIGHT.

41:28.140 --> 41:30.586
- OKAY.

41:30.690 --> 41:32.237
I LOVE YOU.
JUST CALL US WHEN YOU LAND.

41:32.350 --> 41:33.681
- GOT IT.
BYE.

41:33.800 --> 41:38.169
- I'M GONNA MISS YOU.

41:38.280 --> 41:39.212
OKAY.
- ALL RIGHT.

41:39.320 --> 41:42.244
- OKAY.
- SEE YOU ALL.

41:42.360 --> 41:46.706
HI.

41:48.670 --> 41:51.707
[gentle music playing]

42:05.240 --> 42:08.129
[man humming]

42:12.800 --> 42:19.729
DA DA DA DA YA

42:19.840 --> 42:25.392
DA DA DA DA

42:25.500 --> 42:28.196
DA

42:28.300 --> 42:32.054
TA DA DA DA
